TASPathName.name: TASPathName
TASPathName.description: The name of an AS path. An empty string indicates that no AS Path has been specified and is invalid when used as an index for a table.

TCommunityName.name: TCommunityName
TCommunityName.description: The name of a community. An empty string indicates that no community has been specified and is invalid when used as an index for a table.

TCommunityMember.name: TCommunityMember
TCommunityMember.description: The member of a community. Can be one of the following: 1) [1..65535]:[0..65535] 2) An extended community in one of the following formats - target:[0..65535]:[0..4294967295] - origin:[0..65535]:[0..4294967295] - target:<ip-address>:[0..65535] - origin:<ip-address>:[0..65535] - target:[4-byte AS number]:[0..65535] - origin:[4-byte AS number]:[0..65535] 4-byte AS number - [0..4294967295] - target:<regular-expression>&<regular-expression> - target:<ip-address>&<regular-expression> 3) A regular expression 4) A well known community i.e. one of the following keywords - no-advertise - no-export - no-export-subconfed - null.

TCommunityExpression.name: TCommunityExpression
TCommunityExpression.description: TCommunityExpression specifies a logical expression containing terms and operators. It can contain sub-expressions enclosed by round brackets. Terms, operators and brackets are separated by a space character. A term is a string of type TCommunityMember. An operator can be the string 'AND', 'OR', and 'NOT'.

TDampingName.name: TDampingName
TDampingName.description: The name of a route damping policy. An empty string indicates that no damping policy has been specified and is invalid when used as an index for a table.

TPrefixListName.name: TPrefixListName
TPrefixListName.description: The name of a prefix list. An empty string indicates that no prefix list has been specified and is invalid when used as an index for a table.

TPolicyStatementName.name: TPolicyStatementName
TPolicyStatementName.description: The name of a policy statement when used as an index to a table.

TRegularExpression.name: TRegularExpression
TRegularExpression.description: A regular expression string. The Regular expression string matches against 1) an AS_PATH string e.g. '100 200 300', 2) a community string e.g. '100:200' where 100 is the as-number, and 200 is the community-value. The regular expression is expressed in terms of a TERM, and an OPERATOR: A term is either: 1) an AS Number 2) a community value e.g. in 100:200, we have three tokens: (i) 100 is the as-number, (ii) ':' is the separator token, and (iii) 200 is the community-value 3) '.' - DOT is a wild-card token which matches with either an AS Number or a Community. The list of operators are: 1) '|' - suggests an alternation. 2) '*' - multiple occurrences of the token. 3) '?' - 0 or 1 occurrence of token. 4) '+' - 1 or more occurrences of token. 5) '(' - is used to parenthesize so that a regular expression is considered as one token. 6) ')' - closes the parenthesis. 7) '[' - used to demarcate range. 8) ']' - closes the box bracket. 9) '{m, [n]}' - suggest that the term can occur anywhere between m, and n times. 10) '^' - matches the beginning of the string - only allowed for communities. 11) '$' - matches the end of the string - only allowed for communities. Note, use only NVT ASCII displayable characters here, no control characters, no UTF-8, etc. The EBNF description for the regular expression string are: 1) reg_ex ::= empty_string | non-empty_reg_ex 2) non-empty_reg_ex ::= bounded_element | ( bounded_element '|' non-empty_reg_ex ) 3) bounded_element ::= ['^'] element ['$'] 4) element ::= ( '(' list ')' | atomic ) ['*' | '?' | '+' | '{' integer ',' [ integer ] '}' ] [element] 5) list ::= element | (element '|' list) 6) atomic ::= '.' | ':' | '<' | '>' | atom_list 7) atom_list ::= atom | ( '[' atom_list_boxed ) 8) atom_list_boxed ::= ( atom ']' ) | ( atom atom_list_boxed ) 9) (for as-path reg-ex) atom ::= integer [ '-' integer ] an atom is essentially EQUIVALENT to a TERM (for community reg-ex) atom ::= digit[ '-' digit ] NOTE -> atom_list_boxed is a list of integers ending in box bracket - BNF description is error-free.

TPolicyStatementEntryID.name: TPolicyStatementEntryID
TPolicyStatementEntryID.description: Identification number for a policy statement entry. Entries are sorted by ID number. Matching entries are evaluated in order from lowest ID to highest ID. We suggest ordering policy statement entry IDs by 10s: 10, 20, 30, etc., so entry insertions are easy.

TRoutePolicyProtocol.name: TRoutePolicyProtocol
TRoutePolicyProtocol.description: A list of routing protocols, for -to and -from policies.

TOspfRouteType.name: TOspfRouteType
TOspfRouteType.description: The OSPF route type. Set to zero to disable.

TIsisLevel.name: TIsisLevel
TIsisLevel.description: Indicates the ISIS Route Level match criterion. A value of 0 indicates no IS-IS route match criterion is configured. There are two types of areas in IS-IS, namely Level 1 areas and Level 2 areas. Routers within a Level 1 area route to other routers in that area. If the destination does not exist within the area, the Level 1 router will route toward a Level 2 router. Level 2 routers route between areas and toward other ASs.

TPolicyEntryAction.name: TPolicyEntryAction
TPolicyEntryAction.description: Action to take when route matches the entry's match criteria. accept(1) - perform the accept-action modifications, advertise the route, do not evaluate any more policy entries. reject(2) - do not advertise the route, do not evaluate any more policy entries. continue(3) - perform the accept-action modifications, evaluate the next policy entry in the policy statement. nextPolicy(4) - perform the accept-action modifications, evaluate the next policy statement.

TPolicyEntryEdit.name: TPolicyEntryEdit
TPolicyEntryEdit.description: Editing action to take when route matches the entry's match criteria. none(1) - do not change the value in the route add(2) - add the corresponding objects to the route remove(3) - remove the corresponding objects to the route replace(4) - replace the value in the route with the corresponding object.

TPolicyEntryCriteriaOrigin.name: TPolicyEntryCriteriaOrigin
TPolicyEntryCriteriaOrigin.description: Origin of the route. none(1) - ignore this criteria igp(2) - learned from an Interior Gateway Protocol (OSPF, ISIS, etc.) egp(3) - learned from an Exterior Gateway Protocol (BGP) incomplete(4) - Route origin is unknown (usually due to aggregation) any(5) - to or from either igp or egp aaa(6) - subscriber host address originated from aaa dhcp(7) - subscriber host address originated from dhcp ludb(8) - subscriber host address originated from local user database.

TPolicyActionTag.name: TPolicyActionTag
TPolicyActionTag.description: Tag value to set. Zero means disabled, no tag value will be set.

TPolicyEntryCriteriaState.name: TPolicyEntryCriteriaState
TPolicyEntryCriteriaState.description: Generic criteria state. none(1) - ignore this criteria srrpMaster(2) - srrp-master srrpNonMaster(3) - srrp-non-master ipsecMaster (6), - Routes that are in ipsec-master with peer state ipsecMasterNoPeer (7), - Routes that are ipsec-master-without-peer ipsecNonMaster (8) - Routes that are in ipsec-non-master state.

TPolicyActionMetricSource.name: TPolicyActionMetricSource
TPolicyActionMetricSource.description: The source of the Action Metric.

TPolicyEntryAigpMetricEdit.name: TPolicyEntryAigpMetricEdit
TPolicyEntryAigpMetricEdit.description: Editing action to take when route matches the entry's match criteria. none(1) - do not change the value in the route. add(2) - add the corresponding object value to the aigp value in the received route. replace(3) - replace the aigp value in the route with the corresponding object value. useIgp(4) - replace the aigp value in the route with the IGP cost.

tRPOperASPathTableLastChanged.name: tRPOperASPathTableLastChanged
tRPOperASPathTableLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to tRPOperASPathTable. tRPOperASPathTableLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperASPathTable.name: tRPOperASPathTable
tRPOperASPathTable.description: A list of AS Path names and corresponding regular-expressions.

tRPOperASPathEntry.name: tRPOperASPathEntry
tRPOperASPathEntry.description: Information about a particular AS Path Name. Entries are created by user, via tRPAdminASPathTable. Entries are deleted by user, via tRPAdminASPathTable. tRPAdminASPathTable entry must exist before referencing objects {tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPathName, tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPathName, tRPOperPSToCriteriaASPathName, tRPOperPSFromCriteriaASPath} can be set to refer to the tRPOperASPathName.

tRPOperASPathName.name: tRPOperASPathName
tRPOperASPathName.description: The name of the AS Path entry used to uniquely identify an AS Path.

tRPOperASPathRowStatus.name: tRPOperASPathRowStatus
tRPOperASPathRowStatus.description: RowStatus for this row. Values read will only be active(1), notInService(2), notReady(3). To create or destroy entries in this table, use the tRPAdminASPathTable.

tRPOperASPathRegEx.name: tRPOperASPathRegEx
tRPOperASPathRegEx.description: The regular expression for the AS Path entry.

tRPOperASPathEntryLastChanged.name: tRPOperASPathEntryLastChanged
tRPOperASPathEntryLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this entry. tRPOperASPathEntryLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperCommunityTableLastChanged.name: tRPOperCommunityTableLastChanged
tRPOperCommunityTableLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to tRPOperCommunityTable. tRPOperCommunityTableLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperCommunityEntry.name: tRPOperCommunityEntry
tRPOperCommunityEntry.description: Information about a particular community member. Entries are created by user, via tRPAdminCommunityTable. Entries are deleted by user, via tRPAdminCommunityTable. There must be one entry for <community-name><member>, or the <community-name> does not exist and can not be referenced {tRPAdminPSDefaultActionCommunityName, tRPAdminPSAcceptActionCommunityName, tRPAdminPSToCriteriaCommunity tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaCommunity}.

tRPOperCommunityName.name: tRPOperCommunityName
tRPOperCommunityName.description: The name of the community used as an index for this table.

tRPOperCommunityMember.name: tRPOperCommunityMember
tRPOperCommunityMember.description: The AS Number or Community ID of the community member. The community name and the member name uniquely identify a row in this table.

tRPOperCommunityRowStatus.name: tRPOperCommunityRowStatus
tRPOperCommunityRowStatus.description: RowStatus for this row. Values read will only be active(1), notInService(2), notReady(3). To create or destroy entries in this table, use the tRPAdminCommunityTable.

tRPOperCommunityEntryLastChanged.name: tRPOperCommunityEntryLastChanged
tRPOperCommunityEntryLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this entry. tRPOperCommunityEntryLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperDampingTableLastChanged.name: tRPOperDampingTableLastChanged
tRPOperDampingTableLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to tRPOperDampingTable. tRPOperDampingTableLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperDampingTable.name: tRPOperDampingTable
tRPOperDampingTable.description: A table of route damping control entries.

tRPOperDampingEntry.name: tRPOperDampingEntry
tRPOperDampingEntry.description: Information about a particular Damping entry. Entries are created by user, via tRPAdminDampingTable. Entries are deleted by user, via tRPAdminDampingTable. The entry for a damping name must exist before referring objects (tRPAdminPSDefaultActionDamping, tRPAdminPSAcceptActionDamping) can be set to that name.

tRPOperDampingName.name: tRPOperDampingName
tRPOperDampingName.description: The name of the damping entry used to uniquely identify a row in this table.

tRPOperDampingRowStatus.name: tRPOperDampingRowStatus
tRPOperDampingRowStatus.description: RowStatus for this row. Values read will only be active(1), notInService(2), notReady(3). To create or destroy entries in this table, use the tRPAdminDampingTable.

tRPOperDampingHalfLife.name: tRPOperDampingHalfLife
tRPOperDampingHalfLife.description: Specifies the half-life, in minutes, for a routes figure-of-merit after it has been dampened. If a route's half-life is set to 15 minutes and has a figure-of-merit of 1500, after 15 minutes, the route's figure-of-merit will have decayed to 750. Set to 0 to disable.

tRPOperDampingMaxSuppress.name: tRPOperDampingMaxSuppress
tRPOperDampingMaxSuppress.description: Specifies the maximum amount of time, in minutes, that a route can be suppressed for. Set to 0 to disable.

tRPOperDampingReuse.name: tRPOperDampingReuse
tRPOperDampingReuse.description: Specifies the reuse threshold. If a route's figure-of-merit falls below the reuse threshold, the route can be reused. Set to 0 to disable.

tRPOperDampingSuppress.name: tRPOperDampingSuppress
tRPOperDampingSuppress.description: Specifies the suppress threshold. If a route's figure-of-merit goes above the suppress threshold, the route should be suppressed. Set to 0 to disable.

tRPOperDampingEntryLastChanged.name: tRPOperDampingEntryLastChanged
tRPOperDampingEntryLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this entry. tRPOperDampingEntryLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperPrefixListTableLastChanged.name: tRPOperPrefixListTableLastChanged
tRPOperPrefixListTableLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to tRPOperPrefixListTable. tRPOperPrefixListTableLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperPrefixListEntry.name: tRPOperPrefixListEntry
tRPOperPrefixListEntry.description: Information about a particular prefix list. Entries are created by user via tRPAdminPrefixListTable. Entries are deleted by user via tRPAdminPrefixListTable. A prefix list name entry must exist before referring objects (tRPAdminPSToCriteriaNeighborPrefixList, tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaNeighborPrefixList, tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList1 - 5 tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaPrefixList1 - 5) can be set to that name.

tRPOperPrefixListName.name: tRPOperPrefixListName
tRPOperPrefixListName.description: The name of the prefix list entry.

tRPOperPrefixListIpPrefix.name: tRPOperPrefixListIpPrefix
tRPOperPrefixListIpPrefix.description: The IP prefix of the prefix list entry.

tRPOperPrefixListMask.name: tRPOperPrefixListMask
tRPOperPrefixListMask.description: The IP mask length of the prefix list entry.

tRPOperPrefixListRowStatus.name: tRPOperPrefixListRowStatus
tRPOperPrefixListRowStatus.description: RowStatus for this row. Values read will only be active(1), notInService(2), notReady(3). To create or destroy entries in this table, use the tRPAdminPrefixListTable.

tRPOperPrefixListType.name: tRPOperPrefixListType
tRPOperPrefixListType.description: The type of the prefix length entry. exact (1) - a route's prefix/length must match the prefix-list entry exactly in order for an entry to be considered a match. longer (2) - a route's prefix/length must match the defined prefix AND have a length that is an exact match or longer in order for an entry to be considered a match. through (3) - a route's prefix/length must match the defined prefix AND have a length that is an exact match or longer up to and including the defined maximum length in order for an entry to be considered a match. range (4) - a route's prefix/length must match the defined prefix AND have a length that is greater than or equal to the length defined by tRPOperPrefixListBeginLength and less than or equal to the length defined by tRPOperPrefixListThroughLength in order for an entry to be considered a match.

tRPOperPrefixListThroughLength.name: tRPOperPrefixListThroughLength
tRPOperPrefixListThroughLength.description: When tRPOperPrefixListType set to through(3), the mask length to use. Must be larger than tRPOperPrefixListMask.

tRPOperPrefixListEntryLastChanged.name: tRPOperPrefixListEntryLastChanged
tRPOperPrefixListEntryLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this entry. tRPOperPrefixListEntryLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperPrefixListBeginLength.name: tRPOperPrefixListBeginLength
tRPOperPrefixListBeginLength.description: When tRPOperPrefixListType set to range(4), the mask length to use as the lower limit for the mask range. Must be larger than tRPOperPrefixListMask and less than tRPOperPrefixListThroughLength.

tRPOperPolicyStatementTableLastChanged.name: tRPOperPolicyStatementTableLastChanged
tRPOperPolicyStatementTableLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to tRPOperPolicyStatementTable. tRPOperPolicyStatementTableLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperPolicyStatementEntry.name: tRPOperPolicyStatementEntry
tRPOperPolicyStatementEntry.description: Information about a particular policy-statement. Entries are created by user via tRPAdminPolicyStatementTable. Entries are deleted by user via tRPAdminPolicyStatementTable.

tRPOperPolicyStatementName.name: tRPOperPolicyStatementName
tRPOperPolicyStatementName.description: The name of this policy statement that uniquely identifies an entry in this table.

tRPOperPolicyStatementRowStatus.name: tRPOperPolicyStatementRowStatus
tRPOperPolicyStatementRowStatus.description: RowStatus for this row. Values read will only be active(1), notInService(2), notReady(3). To create or destroy entries in this table, use the tRPAdminPolicyStatementTable.

tRPOperPolicyStatementDefaultAction.name: tRPOperPolicyStatementDefaultAction
tRPOperPolicyStatementDefaultAction.description: The default-action for the policy statement indicates what happens to the route if none of the policy statement entries match.

tRPOperPolicyStatementEntryLastChanged.name: tRPOperPolicyStatementEntryLastChanged
tRPOperPolicyStatementEntryLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this entry. tRPOperPolicyStatementEntryLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionParamsTableLastCha.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionParamsTableLastChanged
tRPOperPSDefaultActionParamsTableLastCha.description: Timestamp of last change to tRPOperPSDefaultActionParamsTable. tRPOperPSDefaultActionParamsTableLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionParamsTable.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionParamsTable
tRPOperPSDefaultActionParamsTable.description: Default action parameters for a policy-statement.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionParamsEntry.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionParamsEntry
tRPOperPSDefaultActionParamsEntry.description: Default action information about a particular policy statement. These parameters are applied when the default action for the policy statement is 'accept' (tRPOperPolicyStatementDefaultAction == accept(1)). These parameters are ignored when default action for the policy statement is 'reject' (tRPOperPolicyStatementDefaultAction == reject(2)). Entries are created when a policy statement is created. Entries are deleted when a policy statement is destroyed.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPath.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPath
tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPath.description: The AS Path rewrite information for the route.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPathName.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPathName
tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPathName.description: The AS Path name to use for add, remove, or replace operation specified by tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPath. Ignored when tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPath is none(1).

tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPathPrependAS.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPathPrependAS
tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPathPrependAS.description: AS Number to prepend to the AS-Path attribute of the route. Ignored when tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPathPrependCount is zero. This object was obsoleted in release 7.0. It is replaced with the 4-byte AS number defined by tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPathPend.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPathPrependCount.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPathPrependCount
tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPathPrependCount.description: Number of times tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPathPend is prepended to the AS-Path attribute of the route. Set to zero to disable.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionCommunity1.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionCommunity1
tRPOperPSDefaultActionCommunity1.description: How to apply tRPOperPSDefaultActionCommunityName1 to the communities for the route. Set to none(1) to disable this feature.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionCommunityName1.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionCommunityName1
tRPOperPSDefaultActionCommunityName1.description: Community name to add, remove, or replace, to any existing community for the route. Ignored when tRPOperPSDefaultActionCommunity1 is none(1)

tRPOperPSDefaultActionCommunity2.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionCommunity2
tRPOperPSDefaultActionCommunity2.description: How to apply tRPOperPSDefaultActionCommunityName2 to the communities for the route. Set to none(1) to disable this feature.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionCommunityName2.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionCommunityName2
tRPOperPSDefaultActionCommunityName2.description: Community name to add, remove, or replace, to any existing community for the route. Ignored when tRPOperPSDefaultActionCommunity2 is none(1)

tRPOperPSDefaultActionOrigin.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionOrigin
tRPOperPSDefaultActionOrigin.description: The value of tRPOperPSDefaultActionOrigin indicates the origin of the route exported into BGP if it does not match an entry.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionLocalPreferenceSet.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionLocalPreferenceSet
tRPOperPSDefaultActionLocalPreferenceSet.description: When set to true(1), use the value of tRPOperPSDefaultActionLocalPreference for local preference.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionLocalPreference.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionLocalPreference
tRPOperPSDefaultActionLocalPreference.description: Local preference to apply to the route. Set tRPOperPSDefaultActionLocalPreferenceSet to false(2) to disable.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionMetricValue.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionMetricValue
tRPOperPSDefaultActionMetricValue.description: Add, subtract, or set metric value. Ignored when tRPOperPSDefaultActionMetric is none(1).

tRPOperPSDefaultActionPreference.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionPreference
tRPOperPSDefaultActionPreference.description: Preference to apply to the route.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionDamping.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionDamping
tRPOperPSDefaultActionDamping.description: Damping to apply to route. Set to empty string to disable.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionNextHopSelf.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionNextHopSelf
tRPOperPSDefaultActionNextHopSelf.description: The value of tRPOperPSDefaultActionNextHopSelf indicates the next-hop-self on the route. Next-hop-self cannot be 'true' when the next-hop object 'tRPOperPSDefActInetNextHop' has a valid IP address. If tRPOperPSDefaultActionNextHopSelf has a value of 'true' then tRPOperPSDefActInetNextHop object is disabled.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionNextHop.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionNextHop
tRPOperPSDefaultActionNextHop.description: Set next-hop address in route. Set to 255.255.255.255 to disable. Next-hop cannot be set to a valid IP address at the same time as setting next-hop-self to 'true'. Setting next-hop to a valid IP address will reset next-hop-self to 'false'.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionTag.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionTag
tRPOperPSDefaultActionTag.description: The value of tRPOperPSDefaultActionTag indicates the operational tag for the route. A value of 0 for tRPAdminPSDefaultActionTag indicates that tagging is disabled.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionOspfType.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionOspfType
tRPOperPSDefaultActionOspfType.description: OSPF route type for the route.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionParamsEntryLastCha.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionParamsEntryLastChanged
tRPOperPSDefaultActionParamsEntryLastCha.description: Timestamp of last change to this entry. tRPOperPSDefaultActionParamsEntryLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperPSDefActInetNextHopType.name: tRPOperPSDefActInetNextHopType
tRPOperPSDefActInetNextHopType.description: The value of tRPOperPSDefActInetNextHopType indicates the type of tRPOperPSDefActInetNextHop address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB.

tRPOperPSDefActInetNextHop.name: tRPOperPSDefActInetNextHop
tRPOperPSDefActInetNextHop.description: The value of tRPOperPSDefActInetNextHop indicates the next-hop IP address in the route. The object tRPOperPSDefActInetNextHop is disabled if it holds the value ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff. The type of this address is determined by the value of tRPOperPSDefActInetNextHopType object. Next-hop cannot be a valid IP address when next-hop-self object 'tRPOperPSDefaultActionNextHopSelf' is set to 'true'. If next-hop is a valid IP address then tRPOperPSDefaultActionNextHopSelf is set to 'false'. tRPOperPSDefActInetNextHop object replaces tRPOperPSDefaultActionNextHop that supports only IPv4 address style next-hop.

tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPathPend.name: tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPathPend
tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPathPend.description: The value of tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPathPend indicates the AS Number to prepend to the AS-Path attribute of the route. Value of this object is ignored when tRPOperPSDefaultActionASPathPrependCount is zero.

tRPOperPSDefActMcRedirSvcId.name: tRPOperPSDefActMcRedirSvcId
tRPOperPSDefActMcRedirSvcId.description: The value of tRPOperPSDefActMcRedirSvcId indicates the service ID of the service where to redirect IGMP multicast traffic to. The value zero means that no multicast redirection is configured.

tRPOperPSDefActMcRedirIfIndex.name: tRPOperPSDefActMcRedirIfIndex
tRPOperPSDefActMcRedirIfIndex.description: The value of tRPOperPSDefActMcRedirIfIndex indicates the interface index of the interface where to redirect IGMP multicast traffic to. The value zero means that no multicast redirection is configured.

tRPOperPSDefActionMetricSource.name: tRPOperPSDefActionMetricSource
tRPOperPSDefActionMetricSource.description: The value of tRPOperPSDefActionMetricSource indicates the source of the default action metric. The value 'igpCost(1)' means that the value of MED (Multi Exit Discriminator) or the metric value is derived from the IGP (Interior Gateway Protocol) cost of the route and the value of the object tRPOperPSDefaultActionMetricValue is ignored. The value 'metricVal(2)' means the metric value is the value of tRPOperPSDefaultActionMetricValue.

tRPOperPSDefActionAigpMetric.name: tRPOperPSDefActionAigpMetric
tRPOperPSDefActionAigpMetric.description: The value of tRPOperPSDefActionAigpMetric indicates the editing action to be taken for the AIGP (Accumulated IGP) attribute when the route satisfies the match criteria of the policy. When the value of tRPOperPSDefActionAigpMetric is set to 'none(1)' or 'useIgp(4)', the value of tRPOperPSDefActnAigpMetricVal is ignored.

tRPOperPSDefActnAigpMetricVal.name: tRPOperPSDefActnAigpMetricVal
tRPOperPSDefActnAigpMetricVal.description: The value of tRPOperPSDefActnAigpMetricVal indicates the value to be added or set for the route AIGP(Accumulated IGP) metric. When the value of tRPOperPSDefActionAigpMetric is set to 'none(1)' or 'useIgp(4)', the value of tRPOperPSDefActnAigpMetricVal is ignored.

tRPOperPSParamsTableLastChanged.name: tRPOperPSParamsTableLastChanged
tRPOperPSParamsTableLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to tRPOperPSParamsTable. tRPOperPSParamsTableLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperPSParamsTable.name: tRPOperPSParamsTable
tRPOperPSParamsTable.description: A table of policy statement entries.

tRPOperPSParamsEntry.name: tRPOperPSParamsEntry
tRPOperPSParamsEntry.description: Information about a particular policy statement entry. Entries are created when a policy statement parameters entry is created. Entries are deleted when a policy statement parameters entry is destroyed.

tRPOperPSNameEntryIndex.name: tRPOperPSNameEntryIndex
tRPOperPSNameEntryIndex.description: Identifier for this policy statement entry.

tRPOperPSParamsRowStatus.name: tRPOperPSParamsRowStatus
tRPOperPSParamsRowStatus.description: RowStatus for this row. Values read will only be active(1), notInService(2), notReady(3). To create or destroy entries in this table, use the tRPAdminPSParamsTable.

tRPOperPSParamsDescription.name: tRPOperPSParamsDescription
tRPOperPSParamsDescription.description: Description for this policy statement entry.

tRPOperPSParamsAction.name: tRPOperPSParamsAction
tRPOperPSParamsAction.description: The action to take when a route matches this policy statement entry's to or from criteria.

tRPOperPSParamsEntryLastChanged.name: tRPOperPSParamsEntryLastChanged
tRPOperPSParamsEntryLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this entry. tRPOperPSParamsEntryLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperPSAcceptActionParamsTableLastChan.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionParamsTableLastChanged
tRPOperPSAcceptActionParamsTableLastChan.description: Timestamp of last change to tRPOperPSAcceptActionParamsTable. tRPOperPSAcceptActionParamsTableLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperPSAcceptActionParamsEntry.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionParamsEntry
tRPOperPSAcceptActionParamsEntry.description: Accept-action information for a policy-statement entry. If the policy statement entry action is 'reject' then all of these objects are ignored. Entries are created when a policy statement entry is created. Entries are deleted when a policy statement entry is destroyed. To Create or destroy entries in this table, use the policy statement entry administrative table (tRPAdminPSParamsTable).

tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPath.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPath
tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPath.description: The AS Path rewrite information for the route.

tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPathName.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPathName
tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPathName.description: AS Path Name to add, remove, or replace. Ignored when tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPath is none(1)

tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPathPrependAS.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPathPrependAS
tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPathPrependAS.description: AS Number to prepend to the AS-Path attribute of the route. Ignored when tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPathPrependCount is zero. This object was obsoleted in release 7.0. It is replaced with the 4-byte AS number defined by tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPathPend.

tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPathPrependCount.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPathPrependCount
tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPathPrependCount.description: Number of times to prepend tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPathPend to the route. Set to zero to disable this feature.

tRPOperPSAcceptActionCommunity1.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionCommunity1
tRPOperPSAcceptActionCommunity1.description: How to apply tRPOperPSAcceptActionCommunityName1 to the route.

tRPOperPSAcceptActionCommunityName1.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionCommunityName1
tRPOperPSAcceptActionCommunityName1.description: Community to apply to the route. Ignored when tRPOperPSAcceptActionCommunity1 is set to none(1).

tRPOperPSAcceptActionCommunity2.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionCommunity2
tRPOperPSAcceptActionCommunity2.description: How to apply tRPOperPSAcceptActionCommunityName2 to the route.

tRPOperPSAcceptActionCommunityName2.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionCommunityName2
tRPOperPSAcceptActionCommunityName2.description: Community to apply to the route. Ignored when tRPOperPSAcceptActionCommunity2 is set to none(1).

tRPOperPSAcceptActionOrigin.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionOrigin
tRPOperPSAcceptActionOrigin.description: The value of tRPOperPSAcceptActionOrigin indicates the origin of the route exported into BGP if it matches an entry.

tRPOperPSAcceptActionLocalPreferenceSet.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionLocalPreferenceSet
tRPOperPSAcceptActionLocalPreferenceSet.description: When set to true(1), use tRPOperPSAcceptActionLocalPreference for the local preference for the route.

tRPOperPSAcceptActionLocalPreference.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionLocalPreference
tRPOperPSAcceptActionLocalPreference.description: Local preference for the route. Ignored when tRPOperPSAcceptActionLocalPreferenceSet is false(2).

tRPOperPSAcceptActionMetric.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionMetric
tRPOperPSAcceptActionMetric.description: How to apply tRPOperPSAcceptActionMetricValue to the route.

tRPOperPSAcceptActionMetricValue.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionMetricValue
tRPOperPSAcceptActionMetricValue.description: Value to add, subtract, or set for the route metric. Ignored when tRPOperPSAcceptActionMetric is none(1).

tRPOperPSAcceptActionDamping.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionDamping
tRPOperPSAcceptActionDamping.description: Damping to apply to route. Set to empty string to disable.

tRPOperPSAcceptActionNextHopSelf.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionNextHopSelf
tRPOperPSAcceptActionNextHopSelf.description: The value of tRPOperPSAcceptActionNextHopSelf indicates the next-hop-self on the route. Next-hop-self cannot be 'true' when the next-hop object 'tRPOperPSAcptActInetNextHop' has a valid IP address. If tRPOperPSAcceptActionNextHopSelf has a value of 'true' then tRPOperPSAcptActInetNextHop object is disabled.

tRPOperPSAcceptActionNextHop.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionNextHop
tRPOperPSAcceptActionNextHop.description: Set next-hop address in route. Set to 255.255.255.255 to disable. Next-hop cannot be set to a valid IP address at the same time as setting next-hop-self to 'true'. Setting next-hop to a valid IP address will reset next-hop-self to 'false'.

tRPOperPSAcceptActionTag.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionTag
tRPOperPSAcceptActionTag.description: The value of tRPOperPSAcceptActionTag indicates the operational tag for the route. A value of 0 for tRPAdminPSAcceptActionTag indicates that tagging is disabled.

tRPOperPSAcceptActionOspfType.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionOspfType
tRPOperPSAcceptActionOspfType.description: OSPF route type to set in route.

tRPOperPSAcceptActionParamsEntryLastChan.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionParamsEntryLastChanged
tRPOperPSAcceptActionParamsEntryLastChan.description: Timestamp of last change to this entry. tRPOperPSAcceptActionParamsEntryLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperPSAcptActInetNextHopType.name: tRPOperPSAcptActInetNextHopType
tRPOperPSAcptActInetNextHopType.description: The value of tRPOperPSAcptActInetNextHopType indicates the type of tRPOperPSAcptActInetNextHop address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB.

tRPOperPSAcptActInetNextHop.name: tRPOperPSAcptActInetNextHop
tRPOperPSAcptActInetNextHop.description: The value of tRPOperPSAcptActInetNextHop indicates the next-hop IP address in the route. Next-hop is disabled if the value of tRPOperPSAcptActInetNextHopType is 'ipv6' and the value of tRPOperPSAcptActInetNextHop is ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff. The type of this address is determined by the value of tRPOperPSAcptActInetNextHopType object. Next-hop cannot be a valid IP address when next-hop-self object 'tRPOperPSAcceptActionNextHopSelf' is set to 'true'. If next-hop is a valid IP address then tRPOperPSAcceptActionNextHopSelf is set to 'false'. tRPOperPSAcptActInetNextHop object replaces tRPOperPSAcceptActionNextHop that supports only IPv4 address style next-hop.

tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPathPend.name: tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPathPend
tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPathPend.description: The value of tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPathPend indicates the AS Number to prepend to the AS-Path attribute of the route. Value of this object is ignored when tRPOperPSAcceptActionASPathPrependCount is zero.

tRPOperPSAcptActMcRedirSvcId.name: tRPOperPSAcptActMcRedirSvcId
tRPOperPSAcptActMcRedirSvcId.description: The value of tRPOperPSAcptActMcRedirSvcId indicates the service ID of the service where to redirect IGMP multicast traffic to. The value zero means that no multicast redirection is configured.

tRPOperPSAcptActMcRedirIfIndex.name: tRPOperPSAcptActMcRedirIfIndex
tRPOperPSAcptActMcRedirIfIndex.description: The value of tRPOperPSAcptActMcRedirIfIndex indicates the interface index of the interface where to redirect IGMP multicast traffic to. The value zero means that no multicast redirection is configured.

tRPOperPSAcptActnMetricSource.name: tRPOperPSAcptActnMetricSource
tRPOperPSAcptActnMetricSource.description: The value of tRPOperPSAcptActnMetricSource indicates the source of the accept action metric. The value 'igpCost(1)' means that the value of MED (Multi Exit Discriminator) or the metric value is derived from the IGP (Interior Gateway Protocol) cost of the route and the value of the object tRPOperPSAcceptActionMetricValue is ignored. The value 'metricVal(2)' means the metric value is the value of tRPOperPSAcceptActionMetricValue.

tRPOperPSAcptActionAigpMetric.name: tRPOperPSAcptActionAigpMetric
tRPOperPSAcptActionAigpMetric.description: The value of tRPOperPSAcptActionAigpMetric indicates the editing action to be taken for the AIGP (Accumulated IGP) attribute when the route satisfies the match criteria of the policy. When the value of tRPOperPSAcptActionAigpMetric is set to 'none(1)' or 'useIgp(4)', the value of tRPOperPSAcptActnAigpMetricVal is ignored.

tRPOperPSAcptActnAigpMetricVal.name: tRPOperPSAcptActnAigpMetricVal
tRPOperPSAcptActnAigpMetricVal.description: The value of tRPOperPSAcptActnAigpMetricVal indicates the value to be added or set for the route AIGP(Accumulated IGP) metric. When the value of tRPOperPSAcptActionAigpMetric is set to 'none(1)' or 'useIgp(4)', the value of tRPOperPSAcptActnAigpMetricVal is ignored.

tRPOperPSToCriteriaTableLastChanged.name: tRPOperPSToCriteriaTableLastChanged
tRPOperPSToCriteriaTableLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to tRPOperPSToCriteriaTable. tRPOperPSToCriteriaTableLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperPSToCriteriaTable.name: tRPOperPSToCriteriaTable
tRPOperPSToCriteriaTable.description: A table of policy statement entry 'to' criteria

tRPOperPSToCriteriaEntry.name: tRPOperPSToCriteriaEntry
tRPOperPSToCriteriaEntry.description: Information about a policy statement entry's -to- criteria. Entries are created when a policy statement entry is created. Entries are deleted when a policy statement entry is destroyed.

tRPOperPSToCriteriaRowStatus.name: tRPOperPSToCriteriaRowStatus
tRPOperPSToCriteriaRowStatus.description: RowStatus for this row. Values read will only be active(1), notInService(2), notReady(3). To create or destroy entries in this table, use the tRPAdminPSToCriteriaTable.

tRPOperPSToCriteriaProtocol.name: tRPOperPSToCriteriaProtocol
tRPOperPSToCriteriaProtocol.description: The protocol name to match on. Set to none(1) to disable.

tRPOperPSToCriteriaNeighborIpAddr.name: tRPOperPSToCriteriaNeighborIpAddr
tRPOperPSToCriteriaNeighborIpAddr.description: The IP address of neighbor to match on. Set to 0.0.0.0 to disable.

tRPOperPSToCriteriaNeighborPrefixList.name: tRPOperPSToCriteriaNeighborPrefixList
tRPOperPSToCriteriaNeighborPrefixList.description: The name of a neighbor prefix list to match on. Set to empty string to disable.

tRPOperPSToCriteriaEntryLastChanged.name: tRPOperPSToCriteriaEntryLastChanged
tRPOperPSToCriteriaEntryLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this entry. tRPOperPSToCriteriaEntryLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperPSToCriteriaIsisLevel.name: tRPOperPSToCriteriaIsisLevel
tRPOperPSToCriteriaIsisLevel.description: The value for tRPOperPSToCriteriaIsisLevel defines the IS-IS route level match criterion. A value of 0 indicates that no IS-IS route level match criterion has been configured.

tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList1.name: tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList1
tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList1.description: The value of tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList1 specifies the name of the first prefix list to match on. Setting this value to an empty string disables this prefix list as a match criteria.

tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList2.name: tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList2
tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList2.description: The value of tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList2 specifies the name of the second prefix list to match on. Setting this value to an empty string disables this prefix list as a match criteria.

tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList3.name: tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList3
tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList3.description: The value of tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList3 specifies the name of the third prefix list to match on. Setting this value to an empty string disables this prefix list as a match criteria.

tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList4.name: tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList4
tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList4.description: The value of tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList4 specifies the name of the fourth prefix list to match on. Setting this value to an empty string disables this prefix list as a match criteria.

tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList5.name: tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList5
tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList5.description: The value of tRPOperPSToCriteriaPrefixList5 specifies the name of the fifth prefix list to match on. Setting this value to an empty string disables this prefix list as a match criteria.

tRPOperPSToCritNbrInetAddrType.name: tRPOperPSToCritNbrInetAddrType
tRPOperPSToCritNbrInetAddrType.description: The value of tRPOperPSToCritNbrInetAddrType indicates the type of tRPOperPSToCritNbrInetAddr address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB.

tRPOperPSToCritNbrInetAddr.name: tRPOperPSToCritNbrInetAddr
tRPOperPSToCritNbrInetAddr.description: The value of tRPOperPSToCritNbrInetAddr indicates the IP address of neighbor to match on. The object tRPOperPSToCritNbrInetAddr is disabled if it holds the value ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff. The type of this address is determined by the value of tRPOperPSToCritNbrInetAddrType object. tRPOperPSToCritNbrInetAddr object replaces tRPOperPSToCriteriaNeighborIpAddr that supports only IPv4 address style neighbor.

tRPOperPSToCriteriaInstanceId.name: tRPOperPSToCriteriaInstanceId
tRPOperPSToCriteriaInstanceId.description: The value of tRPOperPSToCriteriaInstanceId indicates instance of a version of the OSPF protocol running in the router instance. If the value of tRPOperPSToCriteriaInstanceId is 4294967295, all instances of OSPF protocol are leaked into BGP.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaTableLastChanged.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaTableLastChanged
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaTableLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to tRPOperPSFromCriteriaTable. tRPOperPSFromCriteriaTableLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaTable.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaTable
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaTable.description: A table of from filter criteria for each policy-statement entry.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaEntry.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaEntry
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaEntry.description: Information about policy statement entry -from- criteria. Entries are created when a policy statement entry is created. Entries are deleted when a policy statement entry is destroyed.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaRowStatus.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaRowStatus
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaRowStatus.description: RowStatus for this row. Values read will only be active(1), notInService(2), notReady(3). To create or destroy entries in this table, use the tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaTable.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaProtocol.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaProtocol
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaProtocol.description: The protocol name to match on. Set to none(1) to disable.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaNeighborIpAddr.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaNeighborIpAddr
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaNeighborIpAddr.description: The IP address of neighbor to match on. Set to 0.0.0.0 to disable.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaNeighborPrefixList.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaNeighborPrefixList
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaNeighborPrefixList.description: The name of a neighbor prefix list to match on. Set to empty string to disable.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaPrefixList1.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaPrefixList1
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaPrefixList1.description: The name of the first prefix list to match on. Set to empty string to disable.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaPrefixList2.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaPrefixList2
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaPrefixList2.description: The name of the second prefix list to match on. Set to empty string to disable.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaPrefixList3.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaPrefixList3
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaPrefixList3.description: The name of the third prefix list to match on. Set to empty string to disable.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaPrefixList4.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaPrefixList4
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaPrefixList4.description: The name of the fourth prefix list to match on. Set to empty string to disable.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaPrefixList5.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaPrefixList5
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaPrefixList5.description: The name of the fifth prefix list to match on. Set to empty string to disable.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaASPath.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaASPath
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaASPath.description: The name of the AS Path to match on. Set to empty string to disable.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaCommunity.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaCommunity
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaCommunity.description: The name of the community to match on. Set to empty string to disable.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaOrigin.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaOrigin
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaOrigin.description: The value of tRPOperPSFromCriteriaOrigin indicates the route match criterion for an entry.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaOspfRouteType.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaOspfRouteType
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaOspfRouteType.description: The OSPF route type to match on. Set to zero to disable.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaEntryLastChanged.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaEntryLastChanged
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaEntryLastChanged.description: Timestamp of last change to this entry. tRPOperPSFromCriteriaEntryLastChanged is obsoleted in release 5.0. TIMETRA-SYSTEM-MIB::tmnxConfigModify notification is used instead.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaArea.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaArea
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaArea.description: Used when redistributing OSPF routes into other protocols. Specifies the OSPF area that must be matched in filtered routes.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaAreaConfigured.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaAreaConfigured
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaAreaConfigured.description: Specifies if the tRPOperPSFromCriteriaArea has been configured

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaIsisLevel.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaIsisLevel
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaIsisLevel.description: The value for tRPOperPSFromCriteriaIsisLevel defines the IS-IS route level match criterion. A value of 0 indicates that no IS-IS route level match criterion has been configured.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaIsisExternal.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaIsisExternal
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaIsisExternal.description: When tRPOperPSFromCriteriaIsisExternal is 'true', match only External IS-IS routes. If 'false', match all routes. External IS-IS routes are those routes that have been learned from outside the IS-IS domain.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaIgmpHostPrefixList.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaIgmpHostPrefixList
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaIgmpHostPrefixList.description: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaIgmpHostPrefixList contains the name of the prefix list that is used to match the IGMP host IP address. The value of the object will be an empty string if it not set.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaGrpAddrPrefixList.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaGrpAddrPrefixList
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaGrpAddrPrefixList.description: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaGrpAddrPrefixList contains the name of the prefix list that is used to match the multicast group address. The value of the object will be an empty string if it not set.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaSrcAddr.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaSrcAddr
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaSrcAddr.description: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaSrcAddr contains the IP address of the source to match on. This object will be used by multicast protocols like PIM and IGMP. The value of this object will be 0.0.0.0 if it is not set.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaInterface.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaInterface
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaInterface.description: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaInterface contains the name of the interface to match on. PIM Bootstrap route policy will use this object to accept/reject bootstrap messages coming on the interface specified by this object. The value of the object will be an empty string if it not set.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaTag.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaTag
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaTag.description: The value of tRPOperPSFromCriteriaTag indicates the operational tag to match on. It will only be valid when tRPOperPSFromCriteriaMatchTag is enabled which indicates that route matching based on tags is enabled. A value of 0 for tRPOperPSFromCriteriaTag when tRPOperPSFromCriteriaMatchTag is enabled indicates untagged routes are matched.

tRPOperPSFromCritNbrInetAddrType.name: tRPOperPSFromCritNbrInetAddrType
tRPOperPSFromCritNbrInetAddrType.description: The value of tRPOperPSFromCritNbrInetAddrType indicates the type of tRPOperPSFromCritNbrInetAddr address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB.

tRPOperPSFromCritNbrInetAddr.name: tRPOperPSFromCritNbrInetAddr
tRPOperPSFromCritNbrInetAddr.description: The value of tRPOperPSFromCritNbrInetAddr indicates the IP address of neighbor to match on. The object tRPOperPSFromCritNbrInetAddr is disabled if it holds the value ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff. The type of this address is determined by the value of the tRPOperPSFromCritNbrInetAddrType object. tRPOperPSFromCritNbrInetAddr object replaces tRPOperPSFromCriteriaNeighborIpAddr that supports only IPv4 address style neighbor.

tRPOperPSFromCritSrcInetAddrType.name: tRPOperPSFromCritSrcInetAddrType
tRPOperPSFromCritSrcInetAddrType.description: The value of tRPOperPSFromCritSrcInetAddrType indicates the type of tRPOperPSFromCritSrcInetAddr address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB.

tRPOperPSFromCritSrcInetAddr.name: tRPOperPSFromCritSrcInetAddr
tRPOperPSFromCritSrcInetAddr.description: The value of tRPOperPSFromCritSrcInetAddr indicates the IP address of the source to match on. This object will be used by multicast protocols like PIM and IGMP and is disabled if it holds the value ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff. The type of this address is determined by the value of the tRPOperPSFromCritSrcInetAddrType object. tRPOperPSFromCritSrcInetAddr object replaces tRPOperPSFromCriteriaSrcAddr that supports only IPv4 address style source.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaFamily.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaFamily
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaFamily.description: The bits set in the value of tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaFamily indicate the address families that this condition would match against.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaInstanceId.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaInstanceId
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaInstanceId.description: The value of tRPOperPSFromCriteriaInstanceId indicates instance of a version of the OSPF protocol running in the router instance. If the value of tRPOperPSFromCriteriaInstanceId is 4294967295, all instances of OSPF protocol are leaked into BGP.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaMatchTag.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaMatchTag
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaMatchTag.description: The value of tRPOperPSFromCriteriaMatchTag indicates if tag matching is enabled or disabled.

tRPOperPSFromCriteriaState.name: tRPOperPSFromCriteriaState
tRPOperPSFromCriteriaState.description: The value of tRPOperPSFromCriteriaState indicates the route state match criterion for this entry.

tRPOperPSFromCritASPathGroup.name: tRPOperPSFromCritASPathGroup
tRPOperPSFromCritASPathGroup.description: The value of tRPOperPSFromCritASPathGroup indicates the AS-Path Group match criterion for this entry.

tRPAdminASPathTable.name: tRPAdminASPathTable
tRPAdminASPathTable.description: A list of AS Path names and corresponding regular-expressions.

tRPAdminASPathEntry.name: tRPAdminASPathEntry
tRPAdminASPathEntry.description: Information about a particular AS Path Name. Entries are created by user. Entries are deleted by user. Entry must exist before referencing objects can be set to refer to the tRPAdminASPathName.

tRPAdminASPathName.name: tRPAdminASPathName
tRPAdminASPathName.description: The name of the AS Path entry used to uniquely identify an AS Path.

tRPAdminASPathRowStatus.name: tRPAdminASPathRowStatus
tRPAdminASPathRowStatus.description: RowStatus for this row. Legal values to write are: active(1), notInService(2), createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). To create a row, set this object to createAndGo(4). The value of tRPAdminASPathRegEx must also be set to a valid non-empty string for the row creation to succeed. When tRPAdminControlApply is set to commit(3), the row will actually be created in the tRPOperASPathTable. To destroy a row, set this object to destroy(6). If there are no objects that refer to the entry, when tRPAdminControlApply is set to commit(3) the row will actually be removed from the tRPOperASPathTable. If there are objects that refer to the entry, the destroy SET request will fail with an error.

tRPAdminASPathRegEx.name: tRPAdminASPathRegEx
tRPAdminASPathRegEx.description: The regular expression for the AS Path entry. This object must be set to a valid non-empty string for the row creation to succeed.

tRPAdminCommunityEntry.name: tRPAdminCommunityEntry

tRPAdminDampingHalfLife.name: tRPAdminDampingHalfLife
tRPAdminDampingHalfLife.description: Specifies the half-life, in minutes, for a routes figure-of-merit after it has been dampened. If a route's half-life is set to 15 minutes and has a figure-of-merit of 1500, after 15 minutes, the route's figure-of-merit will have decayed to 750. Set to 0 to disable.

tRPAdminDampingMaxSuppress.name: tRPAdminDampingMaxSuppress
tRPAdminDampingMaxSuppress.description: Specifies the maximum amount of time, in minutes, that a route can be suppressed for. Set to 0 to disable.

tRPAdminDampingReuse.name: tRPAdminDampingReuse
tRPAdminDampingReuse.description: Specifies the reuse threshold. If a route's figure-of-merit falls below the reuse threshold, the route can be reused. Set to 0 to disable.

tRPAdminDampingSuppress.name: tRPAdminDampingSuppress
tRPAdminDampingSuppress.description: Specifies the suppress threshold. If a route's figure-of-merit goes above the suppress threshold, the route should be suppressed. Set to 0 to disable.

tRPAdminPrefixListType.name: tRPAdminPrefixListType
tRPAdminPrefixListType.description: The type of the prefix length entry. exact (1) - a route's prefix/length must match the prefix-list entry exactly in order for an entry to be considered a match. longer (2) - a route's prefix/length must match the defined prefix AND have a length that is an exact match or longer in order for an entry to be considered a match. through (3) - a route's prefix/length must match the defined prefix AND have a length that is an exact match or longer up to and including the defined maximum length in order for an entry to be considered a match. range (4) - a route's prefix/length must match the defined prefix AND have a length that is greater than or equal to the length defined by tRPAdminPrefixListBeginLength and less than or equal to the length defined by tRPAdminPrefixListThroughLength in order for an entry to be considered a match.

tRPAdminPrefixListThroughLength.name: tRPAdminPrefixListThroughLength
tRPAdminPrefixListThroughLength.description: When tRPAdminPrefixListType set to through(3), the mask length to use. Must be larger than tRPAdminPrefixListMask.

tRPAdminPrefixListBeginLength.name: tRPAdminPrefixListBeginLength
tRPAdminPrefixListBeginLength.description: When tRPAdminPrefixListType set to range(4), the mask length to use as the lower limit for the mask range. Must be larger than tRPAdminPrefixListMask and less than tRPAdminPrefixListThroughLength.

tRPAdminPolicyStatementEntry.name: tRPAdminPolicyStatementEntry
tRPAdminPolicyStatementEntry.description: Information about a particular policy-statement. Entries are created by user. Entries are deleted by user.

tRPAdminPolicyStatementName.description: The name of this policy statement that uniquely identifies an entry in this table.

tRPAdminPolicyStatementDefaultAction.description: The default-action for the policy statement indicates what happens to the route if none of the policy statement entries match.

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionParamsTable.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionParamsTable
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionParamsTable.description: Default action parameters for a policy-statement.

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionParamsEntry.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionParamsEntry
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionParamsEntry.description: Default action information about a particular policy statement. When tRPAdminPolicyStatementDefaultAction for the policy statement is accept(1), and no poliy statement entry matches the route, the following default actions are applied to the route. When tRPAdminPolicyStatementDefaultAction is reject, these objects are ignored, and the route is dropped. Entries are created when a policy statement is created. Entries are deleted when a policy statement is destroyed.

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPath.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPath
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPath.description: The AS Path rewrite information for the route.

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPathName.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPathName
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPathName.description: The AS Path name to use for add, remove, or replace operation specified by tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPath. Ignored when tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPath is none(1).

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPathPrependAS.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPathPrependAS
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPathPrependAS.description: AS Number to prepend to the AS-Path attribute of the route. Ignored when tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPathPrependCount is zero. This object was obsoleted in release 7.0. It is replaced with the 4-byte AS number defined by tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPathPnd.

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPathPrependCoun.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPathPrependCount
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPathPrependCoun.description: Number of times tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPathPnd is prepended to the AS-Path attribute of the route. Set to zero to disable.

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionCommunity1.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionCommunity1
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionCommunity1.description: How to apply tRPAdminPSDefaultActionCommunityName1 to the communities for the route. Set to none(1) to disable this feature.

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionCommunityName1.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionCommunityName1
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionCommunityName1.description: Community name to add, remove, or replace, to any existing community for the route. Ignored when tRPAdminPSDefaultActionCommunity1 is none(1)

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionCommunity2.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionCommunity2
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionCommunity2.description: How to apply tRPAdminPSDefaultActionCommunityName2 to the communities for the route. Set to none(1) to disable this feature.

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionCommunityName2.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionCommunityName2
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionCommunityName2.description: Community name to add, remove, or replace, to any existing community for the route. Ignored when tRPAdminPSDefaultActionCommunity2 is none(1)

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionOrigin.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionOrigin
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionOrigin.description: The value of tRPAdminPSDefaultActionOrigin specifies the origin of the route exported into BGP if it does not match an entry.

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionLocalPreferenceSe.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionLocalPreferenceSet
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionLocalPreferenceSe.description: When set to true(1), use the value of tRPAdminPSDefaultActionLocalPreference for local preference.

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionLocalPreference.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionLocalPreference
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionLocalPreference.description: Local preference to apply to the route. Set tRPAdminPSDefaultActionLocalPreferenceSet to false(2) to disable.

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionMetricValue.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionMetricValue
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionMetricValue.description: Add, subtract, or set metric value. Ignored when tRPAdminPSDefaultActionMetric is none(1).

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionPreference.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionPreference
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionPreference.description: Preference to apply to the route.

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionDamping.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionDamping
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionDamping.description: Damping to apply to route. Set to empty string to disable.

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionNextHopSelf.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionNextHopSelf
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionNextHopSelf.description: The value of tRPAdminPSDefaultActionNextHopSelf specifies the next-hop-self on the route. Next-hop-self cannot be set to 'true' at the same time as setting next-hop object tRPAdminPSDefActInetNextHop to a valid IP address. Setting tRPAdminPSDefaultActionNextHopSelf to 'true' will reset tRPAdminPSDefActInetNextHop object to disable.

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionNextHop.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionNextHop
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionNextHop.description: Set next-hop address in route. Set to 255.255.255.255 to disable. Next-hop cannot be set to a valid IP address at the same time as setting next-hop-self to 'true'. Setting next-hop to a valid IP address will reset next-hop-self to 'false'.

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionTag.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionTag
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionTag.description: The value of tRPAdminPSDefaultActionTag specifies the tag for the route. A value of 0 for tRPAdminPSDefaultActionTag specifies that tagging is disabled.

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionOspfType.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionOspfType
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionOspfType.description: OSPF route type for the route.

tRPAdminPSDefActInetNextHopType.name: tRPAdminPSDefActInetNextHopType
tRPAdminPSDefActInetNextHopType.description: The value of tRPAdminPSDefActInetNextHopType specifies the type of tRPAdminPSDefActInetNextHop address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB.

tRPAdminPSDefActInetNextHop.name: tRPAdminPSDefActInetNextHop
tRPAdminPSDefActInetNextHop.description: The value of tRPAdminPSDefActInetNextHop specifies the next-hop IP address in the route. To disable, tRPAdminPSDefActInetNextHopType should be set to 'ipv6' and tRPAdminPSDefActInetNextHop should be set to ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:fffff:ffff. The type of this address is determined by the value of tRPAdminPSDefActInetNextHopType object. Next-hop cannot be set to a valid IP address at the same time as setting next-hop-self object 'tRPAdminPSDefaultActionNextHopSelf' to 'true'. Setting next-hop to a valid IP address will reset tRPAdminPSDefaultActionNextHopSelf to 'false'. tRPAdminPSDefActInetNextHop object replaces tRPAdminPSDefaultActionNextHop that supports only IPv4 address style next-hop.

tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPathPnd.name: tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPathPnd
tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPathPnd.description: The value of tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPathPnd specifies the AS Number to prepend to the AS-Path attribute of the route. Value of this object is ignored when tRPAdminPSDefaultActionASPathPrependCount is zero.

tRPAdminPSDefActMcRedirSvcId.name: tRPAdminPSDefActMcRedirSvcId
tRPAdminPSDefActMcRedirSvcId.description: The value of tRPAdminPSDefActMcRedirSvcId specifies the service ID of the service where to redirect IGMP multicast traffic to. The value zero means that no multicast redirection is configured.

tRPAdminPSDefActMcRedirIfIndex.name: tRPAdminPSDefActMcRedirIfIndex
tRPAdminPSDefActMcRedirIfIndex.description: The value of tRPAdminPSDefActMcRedirIfIndex specifies the interface index of the interface where to redirect IGMP multicast traffic to. The value zero means that no multicast redirection is configured.

tRPAdminPSDefActionMetricSource.name: tRPAdminPSDefActionMetricSource
tRPAdminPSDefActionMetricSource.description: The value of tRPAdminPSDefActionMetricSource specifies the source of the default action metric. When the value of tRPAdminPSDefActionMetricSource is set to 'igpCost(1)', the value of tRPAdminPSDefaultActionMetricValue is ignored and the value of MED (Multi Exit Discriminator) or the metric value is derived from the IGP (Interior Gateway Protocol) cost of the route. The default value of tRPAdminPSDefActionMetricSource is 'metricVal(2)' which means the metric value is the value of tRPAdminPSDefaultActionMetricValue.

tRPAdminPSDefActionAigpMetric.name: tRPAdminPSDefActionAigpMetric
tRPAdminPSDefActionAigpMetric.description: The value of tRPAdminPSDefActionAigpMetric specifies the editing action to be taken for the AIGP (Accumulated IGP) attribute when the route satisfies the match criteria of the policy. The value of tRPAdminPSDefActionAigpMetric decides how to apply tRPAdminPSDefActnAigpMetricVal to the route. When the value of tRPAdminPSDefActionAigpMetric is set to 'none(1)' or 'useIgp(4)', the value of tRPAdminPSDefActnAigpMetricVal is ignored.

tRPAdminPSDefActnAigpMetricVal.name: tRPAdminPSDefActnAigpMetricVal
tRPAdminPSDefActnAigpMetricVal.description: The value of tRPAdminPSDefActnAigpMetricVal specifies the value to add or set for the route AIGP(Accumulated IGP) metric. When the value of tRPAdminPSDefActionAigpMetric is set to 'none(1)' or 'useIgp(4)', the value of tRPAdminPSDefActnAigpMetricVal is ignored.

tRPAdminPSAcceptActionDamping.description: Damping to apply to route. Set to empty string to disable.

tRPAdminPSToCriteriaNeighborIpAddr.description: The IP address of neighbor to match on. Set to 0.0.0.0 to disable.

tRPAdminPSToCriteriaNeighborPrefixList.name: tRPAdminPSToCriteriaNeighborPrefixList
tRPAdminPSToCriteriaNeighborPrefixList.description: The name of a neighbor prefix list to match on. Set to empty string to disable.

tRPAdminPSToCriteriaIsisLevel.name: tRPAdminPSToCriteriaIsisLevel
tRPAdminPSToCriteriaIsisLevel.description: The value for tRPAdminPSToCriteriaIsisLevel defines the IS-IS route level match criterion. A value of 0 indicates that no IS-IS route level match criterion has been configured.

tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList1.name: tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList1
tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList1.description: The value of tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList1 specifies the name of the first prefix list to match on. Setting this value to an empty string disables this prefix list as a match criteria.

tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList2.name: tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList2
tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList2.description: The value of tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList2 specifies the name of the second prefix list to match on. Setting this value to an empty string disables this prefix list as a match criteria.

tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList3.name: tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList3
tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList3.description: The value of tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList3 specifies the name of the third prefix list to match on. Setting this value to an empty string disables this prefix list as a match criteria.

tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList4.name: tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList4
tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList4.description: The value of tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList4 specifies the name of the fourth prefix list to match on. Setting this value to an empty string disables this prefix list as a match criteria.

tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList5.name: tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList5
tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList5.description: The value of tRPAdminPSToCriteriaPrefixList5 specifies the name of the fifth prefix list to match on. Setting this value to an empty string disables this prefix list as a match criteria.

tRPAdminPSToCritNbrInetAddrType.name: tRPAdminPSToCritNbrInetAddrType
tRPAdminPSToCritNbrInetAddrType.description: The value of tRPAdminPSToCritNbrInetAddrType specifies the type of tRPAdminPSToCritNbrInetAddr address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB.

tRPAdminPSToCritNbrInetAddr.name: tRPAdminPSToCritNbrInetAddr
tRPAdminPSToCritNbrInetAddr.description: The value of tRPAdminPSToCritNbrInetAddr specifies the IP address of neighbor to match on. To disable, tRPAdminPSToCritNbrInetAddrType should be set to 'ipv6' and tRPAdminPSToCritNbrInetAddr should be set to ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:fffff:ffff. The type of this address is determined by the value of the tRPAdminPSToCritNbrInetAddrType object. tRPAdminPSToCritNbrInetAddr object replaces tRPAdminPSToCriteriaNeighborIpAddr that supports only IPv4 address style neighbor.

tRPAdminPSToCriteriaInstanceId.name: tRPAdminPSToCriteriaInstanceId
tRPAdminPSToCriteriaInstanceId.description: The value of tRPAdminPSToCriteriaInstanceId indicates instance of a version of the OSPF protocol running in the router instance. If the value of tRPAdminPSToCriteriaInstanceId is set to 4294967295, all instances of OSPF protocol are leaked into BGP.

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaTable.name: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaTable
tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaTable.description: A table of from filter criteria for each policy-statement entry.

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaEntry.name: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaEntry
tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaEntry.description: Information about policy statement entry -from- criteria. Entries are created when a policy statement entry is created. Entries are deleted when a policy statement entry is destroyed.

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaRowStatus.name: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaRowStatus
tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaRowStatus.description: RowStatus for this row. Legal values to write are: active(1), notInService(2), createAndGo(4), createAndWait(5), destroy(6). To Create a row, set this object to createAndGo or createAndWait. When tRPAdminControlApply is set to commit(3), the row will actually be created in the tRPOperPSFromCriteriaTable. If there are no objects that refer to the entry, when tRPAdminControlApply is set to commit(3) the row will actually be removed from the tRPOperPSFromCriteriaTable. If there are objects that refer to the entry, the destroy SET request will fail with an error.

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaProtocol.name: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaProtocol
tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaProtocol.description: The protocol name to match on. Set to none(1) to disable.

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaNeighborIpAddr.name: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaNeighborIpAddr
tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaNeighborIpAddr.description: The IP address of neighbor to match on. Set to 0.0.0.0 to disable.

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaNeighborPrefixList.name: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaNeighborPrefixList
tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaNeighborPrefixList.description: The name of a neighbor prefix list to match on. Set to empty string to disable.

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaPrefixList1.description: The name of the first prefix list to match on. Set to empty string to disable.

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaCommunity.description: The name of the community to match on. Set to empty string to disable.

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaOrigin.name: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaOrigin
tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaOrigin.description: The value of tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaOrigin specifies the route match criterion for an entry.

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaOspfRouteType.name: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaOspfRouteType
tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaOspfRouteType.description: The OSPF route type to match on. Set to zero to disable.

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaArea.name: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaArea
tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaArea.description: Used when redistributing OSPF routes into other protocols. Specifies the OSPF area that must be matched in filtered routes.

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaAreaConfigured.name: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaAreaConfigured
tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaAreaConfigured.description: Specifies if the tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaArea has been configured

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaIsisLevel.name: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaIsisLevel
tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaIsisLevel.description: The value for tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaIsisLevel defines the IS-IS route level match criterion. A value of 0 indicates that no IS-IS route level match criterion has been configured.

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaIsisExternal.name: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaIsisExternal
tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaIsisExternal.description: When tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaIsisExternal is 'true', match only External IS-IS routes. If 'false', match all routes. External IS-IS routes are those routes that have been learned from outside the IS-IS domain.

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaIgmpHostPrefixList.name: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaIgmpHostPrefixList
tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaIgmpHostPrefixList.description: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaIgmpHostPrefixList contains the name of the prefix list that is used to match the IGMP host IP address. This object is set to empty string to disable.

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaGrpAddrPrefixList.name: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaGrpAddrPrefixList
tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaGrpAddrPrefixList.description: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaGrpAddrPrefixList contains the name of the prefix list that is used to match the multicast group address. This object is set to empty string to disable.

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaSrcAddr.name: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaSrcAddr
tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaSrcAddr.description: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaSrcAddr contains the IP address of the source to match on. It is used by multicast protocols like IGMP and PIM. This object is set to 0.0.0.0 to disable.

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaInterface.name: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaInterface
tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaInterface.description: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaInterface contains the name of the interface to match on. PIM Bootstrap route policy will use this object to accept/reject bootstrap messages coming on the interface specified by this object. This object is set to empty string to disable.

tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaTag.name: tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaTag
tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaTag.description: The value of tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaTag specifies the route tag to match on. Routes will only be matched on this value when tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaMatchTag is enabled. A value of 0 for tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaTag when tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaMatchTag is enabled would match untagged routes.

tRPAdminPSFromCritNbrInetAddrType.name: tRPAdminPSFromCritNbrInetAddrType
tRPAdminPSFromCritNbrInetAddrType.description: The value of tRPAdminPSFromCritNbrInetAddrType specifies the type of tRPAdminPSFromCritNbrInetAddr address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB.

tRPAdminPSFromCritNbrInetAddr.name: tRPAdminPSFromCritNbrInetAddr
tRPAdminPSFromCritNbrInetAddr.description: The value of tRPAdminPSFromCritNbrInetAddr specifies the IP address of neighbor to match on. To disable, tRPAdminPSFromCritNbrInetAddrType should be set to 'ipv6' and tRPAdminPSFromCritNbrInetAddr should be set to ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:ffff:fffff:ffff. The type of this address is determined by the value of the tRPAdminPSFromCritNbrInetAddrType object. tRPAdminPSFromCritNbrInetAddr object replaces tRPAdminPSFromCriteriaNeighborIpAddr that supports only IPv4 address style neighbor.

tRPAdminPSFromCritSrcInetAddrType.name: tRPAdminPSFromCritSrcInetAddrType
tRPAdminPSFromCritSrcInetAddrType.description: The value of tRPAdminPSFromCritSrcInetAddrType specifies the type of tRPAdminPSFromCritSrcInetAddr address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB.

tRPAdminPSFromCritSrcInetAddr.name: tRPAdminPSFromCritSrcInetAddr
tRPAdminPSFromCritSrcInetAddr.description: The value of tRPAdminPSFromCritSrcInetAddr specifies the IP address of the source to match on. This object will be used by multicast protocols like PIM and IGMP.
